 :tx/rationale "Create task: SOUND-LIVE-v2: Fix LIVE view retraction handling + formalize retraction protocol as INV-COHERENCE-002. CONTEXT: Both from_datoms() and apply_datoms() skip Retract datoms for LIVE view updates (guarded by if d.op == Op::Assert). A bare retraction leaves ghost values. The original SOUND-LIVE proposed a debug_assert. This upgrade goes further: actually FIX the LIVE view and FORMALIZE the protocol. THREE-LAYER FIX: LAYER 1 (CORRECTIVE): Fix the LIVE view to handle retractions. In apply_datoms(), when processing a Retract datom: if live_view[(entity, attribute)] exists and its value matches the retracted value, REMOVE the entry. This correctly handles bare retractions (the value is gone) and is harmless for retract-then-assert (the subsequent assert recreates the entry). Same logic in from_datoms(). Specifically: after the existing 'if d.op == Op::Assert' block in apply_datoms (line 1124), add 'else if d.op == Op::Retract { let key = (d.entity, d.attribute.clone()); if let Some((existing_val, _)) = self.live_view.get(&key) { if *existing_val == d.value { self.live_view.remove(&key); } } }'. In from_datoms (line 1052), same pattern. LAYER 2 (DEFENSIVE): Add debug_assert in apply_datoms that detects bare retractions under Cardinality::One without the :tx/bare-retraction flag. This catches protocol violations that Layer 1 handles silently. LAYER 3 (FORMAL): Create spec element INV-COHERENCE-002 via braid spec create: 'Under Cardinality::One, every Retract datom for (entity, attribute, value) where the LIVE view shows that value MUST be accompanied by either (a) an Assert datom for the same (entity, attribute) with a different value in the same transaction (state transition), OR (b) the transaction includes :tx/bare-retraction = true (intentional deletion). Bare retractions without the flag are a PROTOCOL VIOLATION. Falsification: any Retract datom that removes a live_view entry without a paired Assert and without :tx/bare-retraction = true.' This is the formal version of ADR-COHERENCE-001 with enforceable conditions. ACCEPTANCE: (A) After retract-then-assert in same tx: live_view shows new value. (B) After bare retract: live_view entry is REMOVED (not showing ghost). (C) INV-COHERENCE-002 spec element exists with falsification condition. (D) debug_assert fires on bare retract without :tx/bare-retraction flag in debug builds. (E) All existing tests pass — retract-then-assert is the common case and works. (F) New test: test_live_view_bare_retract_removes_entry — assert V1, retract V1 in separate tx, verify live_view no longer contains (E, A). (G) New test: test_live_view_retract_then_assert_updates — assert V1, retract V1 + assert V2 in same tx, verify live_view shows V2. (H) New test: test_live_view_retract_wrong_value_noop — assert V1, retract V2 (different value), verify live_view still shows V1. (I) No performance regression — Retract branch is O(1) hash lookup. FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/store.rs (apply_datoms lines 1101-1161, from_datoms lines 1015-1083). TRACES-TO: INV-STORE-012 (LIVE view correctness), INV-COHERENCE-002 (new). BLOCKS: CE-OBSERVE (t-3cf81ce2)."
